install terminator
Run:
  sudo  apt update
  sudo apt install terminator -y

Launch Terminator correctly
Run:
  terminator

These should split the terminal.
Ctrl + Shift + O
Ctrl + Shift + E

To resize terminal splits:
## Mouse Method
Move cursor on the line between terminals.
When cursor changes shape:

* Click and drag
You can resize:
* left/right
* up/down
---

## Keyboard Shortcuts
### Resize mode
Press:
```text id="s0m3kd"
Alt + Up Arrow
Alt + Down Arrow
Alt + Left Arrow
Alt + Right Arrow
```
Sometimes depending on Ubuntu:

```text id="q7v2pl"
Ctrl + Shift + Arrow Keys
```

may also work.
---

## Zoom one terminal temporarily
Press:
```text id="u2g8er"
Ctrl + Shift + X
```
This maximizes current pane.
Press again to restore splits.
---

## Close one split
Move to pane and press:
```text id="w4k9ta"
Ctrl + Shift + W
```

---

## Navigate between splits
Use:
```text id="j6n1yb"
Alt + Arrow Keys
```

Example:

* `Alt + Left`
* `Alt + Right`
* RViz simultaneously.
